-- About the project ---------------------------------------------------------
The addon was originally a project for a software engineering course
(undergrad) at the College of William & Mary.

To discuss licensing or other issues, contact kahowell.

Original authors
- Bert Cortina
- Kevin Howell
- Kartik Verma

-- Prerequisites -------------------------------------------------------------
- Thunderbird 3.1 (may work with other versions)
- PyXPCOMExt - http://pyxpcomext.mozdev.org

-- Compiling -----------------------------------------------------------------
The provided Makefile should work for at least some flavors of Linux.
Otherwise, compile fresh xpt files in the "components" directory and zip the
entire directory up, rename to xpi. Then install per usual.

-- Writing modules -----------------------------------------------------------
Peruse the provided modules and Python (2.6) documentation. That should be
sufficient.
Maybe more info here later...
